# Facade Pattern Rules

## Facade Structure
- Facade classes must be annotated with @Service
- Place all public record DTOs inside facade class
- Facade should only delegate to internal module service
- Convert internal DTOs to public facade records in all methods
- Never expose internal domain objects directly

## Method Signatures
- All public methods return facade record types or primitives
- Accept only primitive types, String, or facade records as parameters
- Never accept or return internal domain entities
- Include proper null handling and validation

## Documentation
- Document all facade methods with JavaDoc
- Specify which events are published by operations
- Include parameter validation requirements
- Document return value meanings and null conditions

